		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>Permaculture is a new thing for me, I only discovered it after discovering the Podcast. Most of my exposure to it is due to Jack Spirko. </p>
<p>That being said, I want to thank him for exposing a lot of the potential pitfalls that come along with seeking knowledge along the Permaculture path. He is exactly right about keeping politics out of the design process. I am an architect (by education)  and I can assure you that the only thing that keeps a building from falling on your head is physics. It doesn&#8217;t matter which party or church you belong to, the laws of physics don&#8217;t care. Permaculture Design is no different, it just has a different set of &#8220;laws&#8221;.</p>
<p>Thanks again Jack, I look forward to sharing Geoff&#8217;s new online PDC experience with you and all the others, and hopefully many more in the future.</p>
</div>

